title: The Chosen: Last Supper Official Trailer (Season 5)
description:
The Chosen Season 5 in theaters March 28
---
I think I'm more excited to deliver this trailer than any we've done. Which isn't a coincidence because I feel the same way about Season Five as a whole. This is our most kick-butt content yet because we cover joy, pain, loyalty, betrayal, excitement, anger, sadness, and fear, sometimes within one episode.

Itâ€™s Holy Week, the most impactful and famous week in human history. Jerusalem is a powder keg with all of Jesusâ€™ followers, enemies, and over a million Passover pilgrims packed into one small place. He shows sides of Himself weâ€™ve never seen till nowâ€”turning over tables, literally cracking the whip, and weeping with heartbreak but also love. He also confuses His followers at every turn...and to what end?

The takeaway for you from this season: Can you believe and follow even when you don't understand?

Yes, itâ€™s sad and heartbreaking because weâ€™re getting closer to the cross, but weâ€™re also going to get to see some of the most iconic and deeply moving moments from Scripture. The triumphal entry, the turning of the tables, the betrayal by Judas, and the Last Supper...all set against the biggest backdrop and sets we've ever used with a new widescreen format that demands to be seen on the big screen. But of course, we continue our obsession to humanize and authenticate everyone involved.

The table is set. I can't wait for you to see this in theaters.

Dallas Jenkins
Creator, The Chosen

title: We Renovated An Old Warehouse Into Our Dream Studio
description:
Thank you to all of you subscribers out there for quite frankly, making all this possible! We canâ€™t wait to make more content for you guys over the coming months (and years) - next up, 2 videos we filmed in Malaysia!! 

HELLO FRIENDS and welcome to another video!! This week we are going to be showing you guys the ins ands outs of our entire renovation process for our new studio/office!! We have been haphazardly running around like chickens with our heads cut off for the last (8) years - and so we finally decided it was time to attempt to make our dream studio/office. And because we are huge fans of HGTV-style renovation content, we decided to renovate an old warehouse from top to bottom and document the entire process (also top to bottom). Weâ€™ve just hit 10 million subscribers on YouTube, and weâ€™re celebrating with the one youâ€™ve all been waiting forâ€¦ Bugatti vs Koenigsegg Carwow drag race! 

Mat and the team have flown out to Dubai to get their hands on these awesome hypercars, and theyâ€™re about to go head-to-head as they race over the quarter-mile for the chequered flag. But which will come out on top? Letâ€™s take a closer look at the stats. 

Starting with the Bugatti, itâ€™s the Chiron Super Sport, which comes with an 8-litre quad-turbo W16 that produces 1600hp and 1600Nm of torque. This power is sent to all four wheels via a 7-speed dual-clutch automatic gearbox, and the car weighs 1,995kg. Following several interior & exterior modifications, the car we have here is valued at Â£5,000,000.

Alongside it, we have the Koenigsegg Jesko Attack. This is powered by a 5-litre twin-turbo V8, and this creates 1280hp and 1000Nm. This power is sent to the rear wheels only via a 9-speed multi-clutch gearbox, and it weighs a whole lot less than the Bugatti, tipping the scales at just 1,420kg! But just like the Chiron Super Sport, it has a price tag of Â£5,000,000. 

So the Bugatti is well up on power, but it weighs half a tonne more than the Koenigsegg! Could the weight difference prove decisive? Thereâ€™s only one way to find out for sureâ€¦ LETâ€™S RACE!

title: Leon Thomas: Tiny Desk Concert
description:
Bobby Carter | February 20, 2025
On the morning of Leon Thomas' Tiny Desk concert, many NPR staffers assumed the show was postponed due to a snowstorm in the D.C. area. Not only did he proactively schedule his coast-to-coast flight but he was also 30 minutes early to the office. With his sophomore album, MUTT, Thomas has planted his flag as the most exciting artist in R&B music today. The Tiny Desk had to happen now; nothing would get in the way of divine timing.

Thomas was destined to be an entertainer â€” he's been doing it for most of his life. His parents were both musicians and introduced him to their world early on. As an actor, he appeared in multiple Broadway plays before becoming a staple on the Nickelodeon network. Under the tutelage of Babyface, he earned his chops as a writer and producer, eventually penning and producing big hits in R&B and hip-hop.

He opens this set with three songs from MUTT and closes with two from 2023's Electric Dusk, including "Breaking Point," which he dedicates to his recently deceased grandfather, the opera singer John Anthony: "This is one of his favorite songs."

title: HIGHLIGHTS Real Madrid 3-1 Man City | Mbappe (3) & Nico Goals
description:
Manchester City were knocked out this seasonâ€™s UEFA Champions League after a 6-3 aggregate defeat to Real Madrid.
Pep Guardiolaâ€™s side were beaten 3-1 in the second leg at the Santiago Bernabeu with Kylian Mbappe scoring a hat-trick for the current European champions.

After a 3-2 defeat in the first leg at the Etihad, City fell further behind in the tie when the Frenchman scored the opener after just four minutes.

And we suffered a further early early setback with John Stones going off injured after just eight minutes while Erling Haaland was unable to feature in the fixture.

Mbappe scored two more either side of half-time before Nico scored his first goal for City in the dying minutes.

In the ICC Champions Trophy 2025, India will play all its matches in Dubai while Pakistan will host the rest of the countries. The tournament has started on February 19 and the Indian team has started its campaign from February 20. A total of 8 teams have been divided into two groups. The first group includes India, Pakistan, New Zealand and Bangladesh. At the same time, the second group includes teams from South Africa, Afghanistan, Australia and England. The final match of the tournament will be held on March 9. The Indian team has won its first match against Bangladesh by 6 wickets. The great match between India and Pakistan will be played in Dubai on February 23. After this, the Indian team will play the third and last match of the group stage against New Zealand on March 2. The top-2 teams of both the groups will qualify for the semi-finals. But before the challenge of Pakistan, the Indian cricket team has made a good start as soon as it won over the Bangladesh cricket team. After this victory, a wave of happiness also ran among the Indian cricket fans. What did the Indian fans say after Bangladesh's defeat? How eager are Indian fans for the upcoming India vs Pakistan match? Why are Indian cricket fans issuing warnings to Pakistan cricket team? Why do Bangladesh cricket team fans now want to defeat Pakistan cricket team? Why are Bangladeshi fans angry with their captain Nazmul Hossain Shanto? To know this, watch this special video of Zee Switch's Chayan Rastogi directly from Dubai International Cricket Stadium, where he is talking to Bangladeshi cricket fans and Indian cricket fans.

title: Satellite Images Reveal The Reality Of Saudi Arabia's $2 Trillion Megacity In The Desert
description:
The world's largest construction project is carving a path through the Saudi desert, but will the 170-kilometer-long megacity known as "the Line" ever become a reality? Journalists cannot freely report from Saudi Arabia, so we analyzed satellite imagery and spoke to experts to separate the vision from reality.

Not only have the cost and the timeline for construction shifted in the sand, but recent reports suggest that thousands of migrant workers have died while trying to deliver Mohammed bin Salman's "Vision 2030."

title: Toronto Emergency Landing: Captain Steeeve Breaks Down ATC & Survivor Footage
description:
On February 17th, a commercial aircraft was forced to make an emergency crash landing at Toronto Pearson Airport. In this in-depth analysis, Captain Steeeve examines the ATC communications, cockpit decision-making, and real footage captured by witnesses and survivors.

We break down the critical moments leading up to the impact, the actions taken by the flight crew, and the emergency response that followed. This video provides expert insight into the challenges pilots face in high-stress situations and what can be learned from this event.

Every year up until its collapse, Credit Suisse would prepare a report that looked at how wealthy the people of countries around the world were. 
Instead of just looking at GDP per capita which calculates how much the average person in an economy produces in market output every year, this report attempted to calculate the net worth of those people to see how good they were at accumulating wealth over time. 
Someone with a high income that is spending everything they make on rent and overpriced food isnâ€™t going to grow their wealth as quickly as someone who has a more modest income, but is paying off their own home and is investing diligently into retirement accounts.
I like to call this the San Fran Tech Bro Conjecture. 
But according to these annual reports the Australian people always looked like that second group of slower more deliberate wealth builders.
Their raw income isnâ€™t as high as here in America, but they were consistently some of the wealthiest people on the planet. 
UBS, which absorbed Credit Suisse following its collapse, recently released the 2024 report and once again Australians had the second highest MEDIAN net worth on the planet. 
They only fell behind Luxembourg which is a European Micronation which you are probably not in the tax bracket to even be aware of. 
The fact that this report tracks the MEDIAN instead of the average net worth is also really important. 
This means that the Australian right in the middle of a line up from richest to poorest is more than TWICE as rich as an American in the same positionâ€¦
